Introduction

In this part, I analyzed changes to landscape of intra-tumoral granulocytes upon p38 blockade by performing differential gene expression analysis and gene set enrichment analysis.

#Loading libraries
knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
library(SingleCellExperiment)
library(MAST)
library(fgsea)
library(msigdbr)
library(ggplot2)
library(patchwork)
library(dplyr)
library(ComplexHeatmap)
library(circlize)
library(Seurat)
library(ggsignif)
library(knitr)

#Read the sce objected containing immune cell populations
sce <- readRDS("20220310_subsetted.rds")

#Subsetting it to contain only granulocytes/neutrophils
sce.neu <- sce[ ,sce$immgenlabel=="Neutrophils"]

#png function
pngfunc <- function(filename = "mypng.png", width=7, height = 7, units = "in",
                    res = 300, ...){
  png(filename = filename, width = width, height = height, units = units,
      res = res, ...)
}

#Converting sce object to seurat
neu.seurat <- as.Seurat(sce.neu, counts = "counts", data = "logcounts")
Idents(neu.seurat) <- "samplename"

Differential Gene Expression analysis

Differential gene expression analysis was performed using [FindMarkers()] (https://satijalab.org/seurat/articles/de_vignette) function from Seurat, with heatmap generated using [ComplexHeatmap package] (https://jokergoo.github.io/ComplexHeatmap-reference/book/a-single-heatmap.html).

#perform dge
diff1 <- FindMarkers(neu.seurat, ident.1 = "4T1-Tu-plus-p38i", ident.2 = "4T1-Tu", assay = "originalexp", slot = "data", test.use = "MAST", min.pct = 0.01, logfc.threshold = 0)
dge1 <- diff1[diff1$p_val<0.05, ]

diff2 <- FindMarkers(neu.seurat, ident.1 = "p38a-ko-H9", ident.2 = "4T1-Tu", assay = "originalexp", slot = "data", test.use = "MAST", min.pct = 0.01, logfc.threshold = 0)
dge2 <- diff2[diff2$p_val<0.05, ]

#heatmap MDSC markers
genes <- c("Cd84", "Jaml", "Anxa1", "Plbd1", "Atf4", "Wfdc21", "Ltb4r1", "Clec4e", "Clec4d", "Pla2g7", "Junb", "Cebpb", "Mmp8", "Ptgs2", "Vegfa", "Mif", "Il1b", "Tgfb1", "Il1f9",  "S100a8", "Arg1", "Nos2", "Ccr1", "Cxcr1", "Csf2ra", "Cxcl2", "Cxcr4", "Ccrl2")

mean_mat <- AverageExpression(neu.seurat, group.by = "samplename",
                              layer = "data", features = genes)
mat <- mean_mat[[1]]
mat <- t(scale(t(mat)))
rownames(mat) <- genes
colnames(mat) <- c("Veh", "p38i", "p38ko")

cluster_anno <- unique(neu.seurat$samplename)

quantile(mat, c(0.1, 0.95))
##       10%       95% 
## -1.099811  1.131706
f1 = colorRamp2(c(-1.1,0,1.2), c("blue","white","red"), space = "RGB")
pngfunc("Plots/QC2/Granulocytes/Heatmap_GMDSC.png", width = 2.3, height  = 6)
Heatmap(mat, 
        name="Expression", 
        cluster_rows = FALSE, 
        col = f1, 
        column_split = cluster_anno,
        cluster_columns = FALSE,
        show_column_dend = FALSE,
        cluster_column_slices = TRUE,
        column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize=6),
        row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize=9),
        column_title_rot = 45,
        top_annotation = HeatmapAnnotation(foo=anno_block(gp=gpar(fill=scales::hue_pal()(9)))),
        show_column_names = FALSE,
        use_raster = TRUE,
        raster_quality = 4
)
invisible(dev.off())
include_graphics("Plots/QC2/Granulocytes/Heatmap_GMDSC.png", dpi = 300)

#Violin plots
#If you only want to plot vehicle and p38i, subset the seurat object
seu.sub <- neu.seurat[ ,neu.seurat$samplename!="p38a-ko-H9"]

pngfunc("Plots/QC2/Granulocytes/Cebpb.png", width = 3.5, height = 3)

VlnPlot(object = neu.seurat, features = 'Cebpb', group.by = "samplename", pt.size = 0) + labs(title = "Cebpb", x = "", y = "") + theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x= element_blank(), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(face = "italic", hjust = 0.5))+ geom_signif(comparisons = list(c("4T1-Tu-plus-p38i", "4T1-Tu"), c("p38a-ko-H9", "4T1-Tu")), test = "t.test" , test.args = list(alternative = "two.sided", var.equal = FALSE, paired = FALSE),
map_signif_level = TRUE, textsize = 7, y_position = c(18, 22), tip_length = 0) + ylim(NA, 25) +
   scale_fill_manual(values = c("gray71", "deeppink", "forestgreen"))

invisible(dev.off())
include_graphics("Plots/QC2/Granulocytes/Cebpb.png", dpi = 300)

Gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA)

Gene set enrichment analysis was performed using [fGSEA] (https://bioconductor.org/packages/release/bioc/vignettes/fgsea/inst/doc/fgsea-tutorial.html) and mosue gene ontology (GO): biological processes dataset as reference.

#Loading Mouse Gene Ontology database: Biological processes dataset from MSIGDB-Broad Institute
m_gene_sets <-msigdbr(species = "mouse", category = "C5", subcategory = "GO:BP")
msigdb_list_go_bp <- split(x=m_gene_sets$gene_symbol, f=m_gene_sets$gs_name)

#Creating a numeric vector of log2FC values from the DGE analysis of p38i vs veh 
ranks <- dge2[,2]
names(ranks) <- rownames(dge2)

#Ranking - arranging in decreasing order of logFC values
ranks <- sort(ranks, decreasing = TRUE)

#Running GSEA using fGSEA
fgseares1 <- fgsea(msigdb_list_go_bp, stats=ranks)

fgseares1 <- fgseares1 %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(NES)) %>% filter(pval<0.05)

df_res1 = data.frame(lapply(fgseares1, as.character), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)

#Barplot
pngfunc("Plots/QC2/Granulocytes/ko_vs_v_gsea.png", width = 10, height = 3.5)
ggplot(fgseares1 %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(NES))
       %>% filter(pval<0.05) %>% head(n=15), 
       aes(reorder(pathway,NES), NES)) +
        geom_col(aes(fill=NES)) +
        coord_flip()+ labs(x="Pathway", y="Normalized Enrichment Score",
                           title="Pathways enriched in p38KO") + 
        theme_minimal()
invisible(dev.off())
include_graphics("Plots/QC2/Granulocytes/ko_vs_v_gsea.png", dpi = 300)
